name: Austin's Best White Wings
author: Lisawas
summary: This is a great appetizer recipe I created after eating White Wings at one of my favorite places in Austin. They are very tasty with or without the cheese.
ingredients: 4  fresh jalapeno peppers, quartered and seeded
2  skinless, boneless chicken breast halves - pounded to about 3/4-inch thickness and cut into 8 strips each
2 slices pepperjack cheese, each sliced into 8 strips
directions: Place quartered jalapenos on a baking sheet, and broil just until they start to brown, about 5 minutes per side
Remove from heat, and allow to cool enough to handle
Stuff each jalapeno quarter with a pepperjack cheese strip, and wrap with chicken and bacon strips, securing with toothpicks
Broil wrapped jalapenos until cheese is melted and bacon and chicken are cooked through, about 5 minutes on each side
Serve on a platter with buffalo wing sauce and bleu cheese dressing for dipping
